<p class="abstract hayMasTexto">EV charging stocks are&hellip;</p><div class="completeText"><p>EV charging stocks are intriguing for three reasons, Al Root writes in this week&#039;s edition of Barron&#039;s. First, the stocks of the four main companies are down more than 43% from their 52-week highs, on average. Second, the business models are sound. And third, the government is coming to help, the author contends. ChargePoint Holdings (CHPT), the most valuable EV charging company by market cap, has already completed its SPAC merger and trades under its own name, the publication adds. EVgo, who is merging with Climate Change Crisis Real Impact SPAC (CLII), is also aggressively building out its own network of fast-charging stations, which it will also operate. Meanwhile, Volta is merging with Tortoise Acquisition Corp II (SNPR) and EVbox with TPG Pace Beneficial Finance (TPGY), Root notes. <a class="reference_link" href="https://www.barrons.com/articles/4-electric-vehicle-charging-stocks-at-fire-sale-prices-51618619555?mod&#61;past_editions" target="new">Reference Link</a></p></div></dd> </div><div class='elementosRelacionadosWrapper '> <div class='clickeable toggleRelated'> <span class='showWord'>Show</span><span class='hideWord'>Hide</span> Related Items&nbsp;<span class='showWord'>>></span><span class='hideWord'><<</span> </div> <div class='relatedContent'> <ul class='globalRelated'> <li class='linkRelTopic_1'> <a href='#rel_1_tab'>Company News</a></li> <li class='linkRelatedRecs'> <a href='#rel_rec_tab'>Street Research </a></li> <li class='linkRelTopic_2'> <a href='#rel_2_tab'>Earnings</a></li> <li class='linkRelTopic_3'> <a href='#rel_3_tab'>Periodicals</a></li> <li class='linkRelTopic_4'> <a href='#rel_4_tab'>On The Fly</a></li> <li class='linkRelTopic_5'> <a href='#rel_5_tab'>Options</a></li></ul><div class='relTopic1' id='rel_1_tab'><div class='story_details_tabs'><ul><li><a href='#tab_rel_noti_1_1'><span>TPGY</span></a></li><li><a href='#tab_rel_noti_1_2'><